        "title": "Google app engine TCP connection Failed",
        "body": "<p>Spring boot application deployed to google app engine and a request to an endpoint respond correctly with hard-coded text as expected. Apart from the default port <code>8080<\/code> exposed, another <code>TCP:8595<\/code> is also exposed where data with be published to that port by tracking devices.<\/p>\n\n<p>The problem is when i tested to get tcp connection with <code>telnet projectid.appspot.com 8595<\/code> i get this response <code>Connecting To projectid.appspot.com...Could not open connection to the host, on port 8595: Connect failed<\/code>, thought locally a connection is made without failure.<\/p>\n\n<p>How can an application hosted in app engine expose ports?<\/p>\n\n<p>Disclaimer: I'm new to App Engine and GCP<\/p>\n",
